            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.insurance.wa.gov/sites/default/files/documents/emergency-order-number-20-01.pdf",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", we went to Pacific Medical Center's Lynnwood office for COVID-19 testing and treatment. Pacific Medical Center did an exam for COVID-19 and determined that my daughter was not in a high risk category that necessitated laboratory testing. Regence did not waive the deductible and now Pacific Medical Center is billing me $203.35 for the office visit.\"",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A lawyer for Regence said that the services billed “only encompassed an office visit.” She explained: “Claims for office visits are payable at 100% if a COVID-19 test has been billed or the office was billed with a diagnosis that indicates a positive COVID-19 test.”",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Some hospitals ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "have complained",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://khn.org/news/congress-said-covid-19-tests-should-be-free-but-whos-paying/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " that large employers with self-funded health insurance plans have been operating under the assumption that they aren’t covered by the Families First Act and don’t have to pay for coronavirus testing at all -- even after the Labor Department ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
